abstract: CHARLESTON, S.C., July 31.--At an icecream festival in Union, S.C., on Saturday, 30 persons were poisoned by eating ice-cream that had been prepared in a brass vessel. abstract: KANSAS CITY, Mo., Aug. 17.--Harry Hill, of New-York, has been chosen referee in the coming Slade-Mitchell prize-fight. abstract: BOSTON, Mass., Aug. 17.--Counsel for the Receivers of the Barnstable Savings Bank obtained from the Supreme Court to-day leave to declare a final dividend. The Receivers have now on hand $167,857, and will ask leave to make a final dividend of 12 per cent.

abstract: HALIFAX, Nova Scotia, Aug. 29.--The heaviest storm since the gale in last March prevails here to-night. The wind is blowing with great violence from the south-east, and rain is falling in torrents. The storm, it is feared, will prove disastrous to the steamer Brantford City, which is ashore at Little Harbor, near Lockport. The gale is blowing directly on the vessel, and will likely break her to pieces on the rocks.

abstract: SIOUX CITY, Iowa, Aug. 29.--Senators Logan, Dawes, and Cameron, of the Special Indian Committee, reached here to-day from their tour of inspection of the Missouri River Indian agencies.
